<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="584" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,643,959]" pageId="3" pageNumber="584">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,353,680,706]" pageId="3" pageNumber="584">Distribution.</emphasis>
<collectingCountry box="[359,426,680,706]" name="China" pageId="3" pageNumber="584">China</collectingCountry>
(
<emphasis bold="true" box="[443,577,680,706]" pageId="3" pageNumber="584">new record</emphasis>
) (
<collectingRegion box="[601,706,680,707]" country="China" name="Xinjiang Uygur" pageId="3" pageNumber="584">Xinjiang</collectingRegion>
). This species is widespread in the Holarctic region, from 
<collectingCountry box="[1357,1436,680,706]" name="Ireland" pageId="3" pageNumber="584">Ireland</collectingCountry>
east to 
<collectingCountry box="[231,301,716,742]" name="China" pageId="3" pageNumber="584">China</collectingCountry>
, currently known from almost half of the 44 European countries, including the European part of 
<collectingCountry name="Russia" pageId="3" pageNumber="584">Russia</collectingCountry>
; it was previously recorded from 
<collectingCountry box="[555,684,753,779]" name="Kyrgyzstan" pageId="3" pageNumber="584">Kyrgyzstan</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Triapitsyn, S. V." box="[696,878,752,778]" pageId="3" pageNumber="584" pagination="1 - 74" refId="ref6567" refString="Triapitsyn, S. V. (2010) Revision of the Palaearctic species and review of the Oriental species of Ooctonus (Hymenoptera: Mymaridae), with notes on extralimital taxa. Zootaxa, 2381 (1), 1 - 74. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 2381.1.1" type="journal article" year="2010">Triapitsyn 2010</bibRefCitation>
), which is adjacent to 
<collectingRegion box="[1122,1223,752,778]" country="China" name="Xinjiang Uygur" pageId="3" pageNumber="584">Xinjiang</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1233,1304,752,778]" name="China" pageId="3" pageNumber="584">China</collectingCountry>
. Elsewhere, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Haliday" authorityYear="1833" box="[151,309,788,814]" class="Insecta" family="Mymaridae" genus="Ooctonus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="584" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hemipterus">
<emphasis box="[151,309,788,814]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="584">O. hemipterus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is recorded from 
<collectingCountry box="[509,613,789,815]" name="Morocco" pageId="3" pageNumber="584">Morocco</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[623,704,788,814]" name="Turkey" pageId="3" pageNumber="584">Turkey</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[716,803,788,814]" name="Canada" pageId="3" pageNumber="584">Canada</collectingCountry>
, and the 
<collectingCountry box="[902,956,788,814]" name="United States of America" pageId="3" pageNumber="584">USA</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Triapitsyn, S. V." box="[971,1154,788,814]" pageId="3" pageNumber="584" pagination="1 - 74" refId="ref6567" refString="Triapitsyn, S. V. (2010) Revision of the Palaearctic species and review of the Oriental species of Ooctonus (Hymenoptera: Mymaridae), with notes on extralimital taxa. Zootaxa, 2381 (1), 1 - 74. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 2381.1.1" type="journal article" year="2010">Triapitsyn 2010</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Huber, J. T." box="[1165,1303,788,814]" pageId="3" pageNumber="584" pagination="15 - 105" refId="ref6245" refString="Huber, J. T. (2012) Revision of Ooctonus (Hymenoptera: Mymaridae) in the Nearctic region. Journal of the Entomological Society of Ontario, 143, 15 - 105." type="journal article" year="2012">Huber 2012</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,398,824,850]" pageId="3" pageNumber="584" type="biology_ecology">
